'''點亮藍燈'''（{{lang-en|Light It Up Blue}}），又名'''點亮藍色'''，在每年[[4月2日|4月2日]]舉行，致力提高大眾對[[自閉症|自閉症]]的認識<ref>{{Cite web|title= Light It Up Blue was not created or owned by Autism speaks, although they have driven awareness of the initiative across the US.|url= http://www.lightitupblue.org/|accessdate= 2020-08-19|archive-date= 2010-03-22|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20100322191630/http://www.lightitupblue.org/|dead-url= no}}</ref>。本活動由{{link-en|自閉症之聲|Autism Speaks}}提出<ref>{{cite press release  |title= Light It Up Blue Campaign to Celebrate World Autism Awareness Day, and what is also Autism Awareness Month in the United States.  |url= http://www.autismspeaks.org/press/light_it_up_blue.php  |publisher= Autism Speaks  |date= 2010-03-17  |access-date= 2020-08-19  |archive-date= 2010-12-28  |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101228085445/http://www.autismspeaks.org/press/light_it_up_blue.php  |dead-url= no  }}</ref>，旨在提高國際對自閉症的認識，以及支持[[世界提高自闭症意识日|世界提高自闭症意识日]]和美國自閉症意識月（{{lang|en|Autism Awareness Month}}）<ref>{{cite video |title= Autism awareness speaks to challenged families |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/21134540/vp/36147981#36147981 |publisher= Today Show|date=2010-04-02}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
全球標誌性地標，包括[[紐約|紐約]]的[[帝國大廈|帝國大廈]]、[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]的[[韋萊集團大廈|韋萊集團大廈]]、[[多倫多|多倫多]]的[[加拿大國家電視塔|加拿大國家電視塔]]，以及機場、橋樑、博物館、音樂廳、酒店、醫院<ref>{{Cite news |title= UMASS MEDICAL SCHOOL PARTICIPATES IN LIGHT IT UP BLUE FOR WORLD AUTISM AWARENESS DAY |url= http://www.umassmed.edu/UMass_Medical_School_Participates_in_Light_It_Up_Blue.aspx |publisher= University of Massachusetts Medical School |date= 2010-04-02 |accessdate= 2020-08-31 |archive-date= 2013-10-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131013032825/http://www.umassmed.edu/UMass_Medical_School_Participates_in_Light_It_Up_Blue.aspx |dead-url= no }}</ref>和零售店在內的美國16個城市，連同全球9個國家/地區的100多個建築物，在2010年4月1日晚上，即美國自閉症意識月（{{lang|en|Autism Awareness Month}}）的首個晚上以及[[世界提高自閉症意識日|世界提高自閉症意識日]]的前夕以藍燈點亮<ref>{{cite press release  |title= Autism Speaks Launches Light It Up Blue Campaign to Celebrate World Autism Awareness Day, Autism Awareness Month in the United States. The project was initiated by, a young man from New York in 2008. Motivated by his personal experience with lack of autism awareness, he dreamed, planned, and outlined his ideas in his application to the Empire State Building. He asked the Empire State Building to light blue for autism in 2008. Blue was chosen for all three tiers of the building as a symbol of hope. He worked for support from Autism Speaks on 2008, and 2009. The dream became a reality, and in 2011 the young man lit up the Empire State Building himself. Since then, countless landmarks and organizations worldwide have joined the movement later named Light it Up Blue by Autism Speaks.  |url= http://blog.autismspeaks.org/2011/04/01/empire-state-building-lights-up-blue/  |publisher= Autism Speaks  |date= 2010-03-17  |access-date= 2020-08-31  |archive-date= 2014-12-09  |archive-url= https://archive.is/20141209172602/http://blog.autismspeaks.org/2011/04/01/empire-state-building-lights-up-blue/  |dead-url= no  }}</ref>。

2010年4月2日，即第三屆世界提高自閉症意識日，{{link-en|自閉症之聲|Autism Speaks}}志願者和支持者在[[紐約證券交易所|紐約證券交易所]]舉行慶祝活動。他們敲響紐約證券交易所的鐘，以此揭開慶祝的序幕<ref>{{cite video |title= Autism Speaks Launches the Light It Up Blue Campaign |url= http://widgets.vodpod.com/w/video_embed/Video.3350577 |publisher= CNBC |date= 2010-04-01 |access-date= 2020-08-31 |archive-date= 2012-10-10 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121010162659/http://media.cnbc.com/i/CNBC/components/Syndicated%20Video%20Player/videoModule.swf?id=1457305587&pcode=cnbcplayershare&play=&base=http%3A%2F%2Fplus.cnbc.com%2Fstickers%2Fpartners%2Fcnbcplayershare%2F |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

2011年，儘管自閉症之聲作出呼籲，但[[白宮|白宮]]表示不會為了紀念世界提高自閉症意識日而點亮藍光<ref>{{Cite news |title= White House Says No To Autism Speaks Effort |url= http://www.disabilityscoop.com/2011/03/04/white-house-autism-speaks/12505/ |publisher= Disability Scoop |date= 2010-03-04 |accessdate= 2020-08-31 |archive-date= 2018-09-25 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180925102958/https://www.disabilityscoop.com/2011/03/04/white-house-autism-speaks/12505/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>。不過在2017年，總統[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]透過將白宮以藍色點亮，履行對蘇珊·賴特（{{lang|en|Suzanne Wright}}，自閉症之聲的共同創始人）的承諾<ref>{{Cite news|title= White House will Light It Up Blue for World Autism Awareness Day |url=https://www.autismspeaks.org/news/news-item/white-house-will-light-it-blue-world-autism-awareness-day |publisher= Autism Speaks|date=2017-03-31}}</ref>。

